{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Gnusto"}],"title":"Splitting a Game Across Files","role":"article","roleHeading":"Article"},"abstract":[{"text":"Keep a large game readable by composing its map and rules from per-region helpers.","type":"text"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A Gnusto game is one type conforming to "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Game","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". That does "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"not","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" mean it must live in one file. A large game splits cleanly along two of its three parts today; the third has a known boundary worth understanding."}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"The one rule: declarations stay in the struct body","anchor":"The-one-rule-declarations-stay-in-the-struct-body"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Locations, items, and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"text":" state are ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"stored properties","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":", and Swift requires stored properties to be declared in a type’s main body — not in an extension. The bootstrap also discovers every entity by reflecting over the single ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Game","type":"reference"},{"text":" type and naming each entity after its property (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"let foyer = Location { … }"},{"text":" becomes ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/EntityID","type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"foyer\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"). So all entity declarations live together, in the file that declares the struct:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["struct OperaHouse: Game {","    let foyer = Location { name(\"Foyer of the Opera House\"); … }","    let bar   = Location { name(\"Foyer Bar\"); dark }","    let cloak = Item { name(\"velvet cloak\"); wearable }","    @Global var disturbances = 0","    \/\/ …","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"(If you reach the point where even the ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"declarations"}]},{"text":" need to span files or ship in a separate package, reach for ","type":"text"},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"content bundles"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — a region declared as its own "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent"},{"type":"text","text":" type. See "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":".)"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"`map` and `rules` compose across files","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"map-and-rules-compose-across-files"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Both "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":" are result-builder properties, and the builder accepts whole "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WorldMap","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" \/ ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Rules","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" values as well as individual entries. That means you can break each one into per-region helper properties and splice them together:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["extension OperaHouse {","    var map: WorldMap {","        foyerMap        \/\/ a WorldMap, defined elsewhere","        cloakroomMap","        barMap","        player.starts(in: foyer)","    }","","    var rules: Rules {","        foyerRules      \/\/ a Rules value, defined elsewhere","        cloakroomRules","        barRules","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each helper is itself a builder property, annotated so its body can use the block syntax. Put each region in its own file:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ OperaHouse+Bar.swift","extension OperaHouse {","    @MapBuilder var barMap: WorldMap {","        bar.north(foyer)","        message.starts(in: bar)","    }","","    @RuleBuilder var barRules: Rules {","        bar.beforeEachTurn { … }","        bar.afterEachTurn  { … }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inside an extension, the bare identifiers ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"bar"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"message"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"player"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"command"},{"type":"text","text":", your "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"type":"text","text":"s) resolve to the same declarations and engine globals they would inside the struct — nothing needs to be passed around."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"A recommended layout for a large game","anchor":"A-recommended-layout-for-a-large-game","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"syntax":null,"code":["MyGame\/","  MyGame.swift            \/\/ struct: all Location\/Item\/@Global declarations,","                          \/\/   plus map { … } and rules { … } that compose the regions","  MyGame+Foyer.swift      \/\/ foyerMap  + foyerRules","  MyGame+Cloakroom.swift  \/\/ cloakroomMap + cloakroomRules","  MyGame+Bar.swift        \/\/ barMap    + barRules"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The struct file stays a readable table of contents — what exists and how the regions connect — while each region’s geography and logic lives next to itself.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Worked example","anchor":"Worked-example","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Tests\/GnustoTests\/Support\/SplitGame\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a minimal game authored exactly this way: declarations in ","type":"text"},{"code":"SplitGame.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", with ","type":"text"},{"code":"gardenMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"\/","type":"text"},{"code":"gardenRules","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in ","type":"text"},{"code":"SplitGame+Garden.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"houseMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"\/","type":"text"},{"code":"houseRules","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in ","type":"text"},{"code":"SplitGame+House.swift","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". ","type":"text"},{"code":"MultiFileCompositionTests","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" boots it and confirms that the map entries and rules from every file take effect at runtime.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"What splits, and how","anchor":"What-splits-and-how","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Part"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Splits across files?","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes — compose from per-region "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Rules","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" helpers."}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"map","type":"codeVoice"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes — compose from per-region "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WorldMap"},{"type":"text","text":" helpers."}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Custom verbs","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes — a game’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"verbs"},{"type":"text","text":" block, and any bundle’s."}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Entity declarations"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In the struct body by default; across types\/packages via ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]]],"type":"table"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The table above is the extension-based split: one "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Game"},{"type":"text","text":" struct, declarations in its body, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":"\/"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"verbs"},{"type":"text","text":" composed from per-region helpers. When a region needs to own its "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"declarations"}]},{"type":"text","text":" too — or ship as a package — promote it to a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto"]]},"sections":[],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gnusto\/splittingagameacrossfiles"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Plugins","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContents","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GamePlugin"],"anchor":"Composing-Large-Games","generated":true,"title":"Composing Large Games"